SUMMARY:DH & ADH [@dhmtg]
DESCRIPTION:1. Courses:\n   1. AC and GT thought to have each course approv
 ed by the CCC.\n   2. HB said already too much time spent on Curriculum Pl
 ans\;\n      better to ask faculty their suggestions to make a core list.\
 n      Then exceptions could be handled by CCC.\n2. Curriculum Cmte Oral E
 xams\n   1. Lesser "volunteered" himself\, but maybe we need a process?\n 
   2. Crosby suggested an examiner bank for each exam.\n   3. ☑ For next fa
 culty meeting:\n      • keep separate from Curriculum changes (Tew).\n    
   • prepare slide with context of current students "in\n        process"\n
         1. C+ in POLYMER 604: self-study\, continue with 704.  Oral\n     
       exam at the end of Spring 2026 semester on 604 subject\n           m
 atter.  Grade in 704 will also be considered as part\n           of demons
 trating proficiency.\n        2. C+ in POLYMER 604: audit undergraduate co
 urses in Fluid\n           Mechanics and in Statics.  Oral exam at the end
  of Fall\n           2026 semester on 604 subject matter.  Proceed with\n 
           POLYMER 704 in Spring 2027 semester.\n        3. C+ in POLYMER 6
 07: audit POLYMER 501 for the chemistry\n           portion and take the c
 orresponding exam.  Grade in 760\n           will also be considered as pa
 rt of demonstrating\n           proficiency.\n      • options for examiner
 s\; open floor for discussion\n        1. Cmte selects both examiners\; po
 tentially both prior\n           instructors.  Student has no agency.\n   
      2. Cmte presents a list of possible examiners.  Student\n           c
 an choose one.  Cmte selects the other.\n        3. Collectively establish
  an examiner "bank" to rotate\n           among faculty members.  Potentia
 l for subject matter\n           mismatch.\n3. +Independent Study in POLYM
 ER+\n   1. Time-sensitive\, but bottleneck with Groth handling everything.
 \n   2. Undergrad Program Director (Ribbe) to handle?  Access in\n      SP
 IRE?
